A group of women is challenging the Ingonyama Trust, in the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. PIETERMARITZBURG - Three million hectares of land in KZN under scrutiny. A group of women is challenging the Ingonyama Trust, in the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. They say they were tricked into signing leases on ancestral land. The Trust Board and the office of the Rural Development and Land Reform Minister came under fire on Thursday, as its practices were put under the microscope. READ: Didiza calls for transparency from Ingonyama Trust board The applicants in the matter say the Trust board acted unlawfully and in violation of the Constitution. The Trust has defended its decision, saying the lease agreement system empowers beneficiaries.The matter is expected to continue at the KZN High Court in Pietermaritzburg.